---
import ProjectLayout from '../../layouts/ProjectLayout.astro';
---
<ProjectLayout title="Reactions">

  <!-- Hero image -->
  <section data-no-reveal class="project-hero-section px-3 md:px-36 lg:px-64">
    <img
      src="/Reactionshero.png"
      alt="LinkedIn Reactions hero"
      class="w-full h-auto rounded-[48px]"
    />
  </section>

  <!-- Overview -->
  <section class="px-3 md:px-36 lg:px-64 py-14 md:py-20">
    <h2 class="text-[2.8rem] md:text-[3.4rem] leading-[1] md:leading-[1.1] font-semibold text-white mt-4 mb-3 max-w-3xl mx-auto">Overview</h2>
    <p class="text-white text-2xl md:text-[1.69rem] leading-snug mx-auto mb-6 max-w-3xl">
      While the reaction menu was being migrated to a new tech stack, I carved out scope for quick visual and interaction design improvements. I added subtle motion by scaling icons in the active state, making interactions feel more responsive and tactile. Visually, I shifted to a circled fill style for better balance and clarity.
    </p>
    <p class="text-white text-2xl md:text-[1.69rem] leading-snug mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      With more time, I would have advocated for a modernized visual language to better align the icons with the overall product aesthetic.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Before / After image -->
  <section class="px-0 md:px-0 py-10 md:py-14">
    <img
      src="/reactionsbeforeafter.png"
      alt="LinkedIn Reactions before and after comparison"
      class="w-full h-[45vh] md:h-auto object-cover object-center rounded-none md:rounded-[40px]"
    />
  </section>

  <!-- Impact -->
  <section class="px-3 md:px-36 lg:px-64 py-14 md:py-20">
    <h2 class="text-[2.8rem] md:text-[3.4rem] leading-[1] md:leading-[1.1] font-semibold text-white mt-4 mb-3 max-w-3xl mx-auto">Impact</h2>
    <p class="text-white text-2xl md:text-[1.69rem] leading-snug mx-auto max-w-3xl">
      While the improvements were mainly targeting design polish, we also saw a modest increase in reactions usage. It turns out good craft is good for business too! The work also got some love from the motion design community on LinkedIn <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/kennyraymond/" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="underline">here</a>.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Reaction motion GIF -->
  <section class="px-0 md:px-0 py-10 md:py-14">
    <img
      src="/reactionMotion.gif"
      alt="LinkedIn Reactions interaction animation"
      class="w-full h-[70vh] md:h-auto object-cover object-center rounded-none md:rounded-[40px]"
    />
  </section>

</ProjectLayout>
